        <mxCell id="portb" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontColor=#333D4D;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="Each failure class earns autonomous authority independently. The three criteria: well-defined signature (the agent can reliably identify this failure type), deterministic fix (the correct remediation is not ambiguous), and contained blast radius (a wrong fix cannot cascade beyond a bounded scope). Meeting only one or two of these conditions means a longer stage 2 evaluation, not early promotion." vertex="1">
